"then I'm going to spend it all on fruit.

00:09:35.328 --> 00:09:36.789
"I can buy 10 pounds of fruit."

00:09:36.789 --> 00:09:40.661
So to say that this right over here is 10.

00:09:40.661 --> 00:09:43.928
Let's say this right over
here is 10, this is 5,

00:09:43.928 --> 00:09:46.156
so this is also on our budget line

00:09:46.156 --> 00:09:48.132
and every point in between

00:09:48.132 --> 00:09:50.220
is going to be on our budget line.

00:09:50.220 --> 00:09:53.599
Every point in between is
going to be on our budget line.

00:09:53.599 --> 00:09:54.800
Another way you could have done this

00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:56.925
and this comes straight
out of kind of your typical

00:09:56.925 --> 00:09:57.878
algebra 1 course.

00:09:57.878 --> 00:10:01.739
You could say, in this case,

00:10:01.739 --> 00:10:02.638
if you view this as the Y axis,

